The arrays define the relative scattered power from the Rayleigh scattering vs. distance along the fiber. The actual data values are recorded in an OTDR file and/or image file, which are referenced in sub-elements.

Classe Java pour FiberOTDR complex type.

Le fragment de schÃ©ma suivant indique le contenu attendu figurant dans cette classe.


 <complexType name="FiberOTDR">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <sequence>
         <element name="DataInOTDRFile" type="energyml.common2_1.String64" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="DTimRun" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}dateTime"/>
         <element name="ExtensionNameValue" type="energyml.common2_1.ExtensionNameValue" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="MeasurementContact" type="energyml.prodml2_0.BusinessAssociate" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Name" type="energyml.common2_1.String64"/>
         <element name="OpticalPathDistanceEnd" type="energyml.common2_1.LengthMeasure"/>
         <element name="OpticalPathDistanceStart" type="energyml.common2_1.LengthMeasure"/>
         <element name="OTDRImageFile" type="energyml.common2_1.String64" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Wavelength" type="energyml.common2_1.LengthMeasure"/>
         <element name="FiberOTDRInstrumentBox" type="energyml.prodml2_0.FiberOTDRInstrumentBox" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Direction" type="energyml.prodml2_0.OTDRDirection"/>
         <element name="ReasonForRun" type="energyml.prodml2_0.OTDRReason" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="uid" use="required" type="energyml.common2_1.String64" />
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

energyml.prodml2_0.FiberOneWayAttenuatio:
The power loss for one-way travel of a beam of light, usually measured in decibels per unit length. It is necessary to include both the value (and its unit) and the wavelength at which this attenuation was measured.

Classe Java pour FiberOneWayAttenuation complex type.

Le fragment de schÃ©ma suivant indique le contenu attendu figurant dans cette classe.

     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <sequence>
         <element name="Value" type="energyml.common2_1.LogarithmicPowerRatioPerLengthMeasure"/>
         <element name="AttenuationMeasure" type="energyml.prodml2_0.AbstractAttenuationMeasure"/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="uid" use="required" type="energyml.common2_1.UuidString" />

   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

         <element name="Value" type="energyml.common2_1.LogarithmicPowerRatioPerLengthMeasure"/>
         <element name="Wavelength" type="energyml.common2_1.LengthMeasure" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>

 </complexType>
